Pulitizer-Prize nominated David Lamb has spent 25 years around the world as an LA Times foreign correspondent. "The Arabs" is based off his 3-year placement 
in Cairo, Egypt, and the insight he gained into the middle east's politics and culture. He elaborates on the effects of the extreme wealth
generated by oil, the state of religion, and examines the history and current political situations of the regions most interesting countries.
This book helped me understand the often frustrating cultural differences I experienced as I traveled through Egypt and Jordan.
