David Lamb's other book, this time based on his experience in Sub-Saharan Africa, or "Black Africa." This book is older 
and hasn't been updated in at least 20 years, but still offers an interesting perspective on one of the most unstable 
and overlooked regions in the world. Lamb has a wealth of unique experiences, from walking into Idi Amin's house right 
after he was overthrown to surviving an Ethiopean figher plane attack on a Sudanese village.
